---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  date: 'January 20, 2025',
  tool1: {
    name: '10Web AI',
    slug: '/reviews/10web'
  },
  tool2: {
    name: 'Durable AI',
    slug: '/reviews/durable'
  }
};

const quickVerdict = {
    tenweb: 'Best for WordPress sites and e-commerce',
    durable: 'Best for ultra-fast simple sites',
    winner: 'Speed: Durable. Features: 10Web. Pick your priority.'
};

---

<Layout title="10Web AI vs Durable AI: WordPress Features vs Blazing Speed">

  <!-- WebPage Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: '10Web AI vs Durable AI: WordPress Features vs Blazing Speed',
      description: '10Web is WordPress with AI. Durable is the fastest AI builder (30 seconds). One gives you 60,000 plugins. The other generates complete sites before you can blink. Here\'s how to choose.',
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/10web-vs-durable'
    }}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              {comparisonData.date} · COMPARISON
            </span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">10Web AI vs Durable AI:</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Features vs Speed</span>
          </h1>

          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              10Web is WordPress with AI generation—60,000 plugins, full e-commerce, but requires WordPress knowledge. Durable generates complete sites in 30 seconds—simple, fast, but limited. One's a powerhouse, one's a sprinter.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <article class="px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900">
            <strong>The one-sentence answer:</strong><br />
            Use Durable if you need a simple site fast (30 seconds fast).<br />
            Use 10Web if you need WordPress power, e-commerce, or extensibility.<br /><br />
            Durable wins on speed and ease. 10Web wins on features and flexibility.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The fundamental difference
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          10Web generates WordPress sites. You get the entire WordPress ecosystem—plugins, themes, WooCommerce, any WordPress developer can help. It's powerful but complex. PageSpeed: 75-85. Build time: 30-60 seconds.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Durable generates proprietary sites optimized for speed. Complete site with CRM, forms, AI copy in 30 seconds. No plugins, no export, locked into their platform. But it loads insanely fast (95+ PageSpeed) and requires zero technical knowledge.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">10Web AI:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.tenweb}</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Durable AI:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.durable}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
            <strong>Verdict:</strong> {quickVerdict.winner}
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Quick comparison
        </h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Metric</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">10Web AI</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Durable AI</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Winner</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Generation speed</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">30-60 seconds</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">30 seconds</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Durable</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">PageSpeed score</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">75-85</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">95+</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Durable</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">E-commerce</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Full WooCommerce</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Basic only</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">10Web</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Export options</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Full WordPress</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">None</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">10Web</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Plugin ecosystem</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">60,000+ plugins</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Built-in features only</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">10Web</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Ease of use</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Medium (WordPress)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">Very Easy</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Durable</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Monthly cost</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$10-60</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$15-20</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Durable</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where 10Web wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Real e-commerce</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Durable has basic e-commerce. 10Web has full WooCommerce—product variants, inventory, shipping zones, tax calculation, 60+ payment gateways. If you're selling products beyond simple items, 10Web is the only option.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Plugin ecosystem</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Need memberships? WordPress has plugins. Need advanced SEO? Yoast. Need forums? bbPress. 10Web gives you 20 years of WordPress innovation. Durable has whatever Durable built.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">You can export</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          10Web exports standard WordPress. Move to any host, hire any developer. Durable doesn't export at all—you're locked in permanently. If client work or potential exit matters, 10Web wins.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Content sites</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          For blogs, news sites, documentation—WordPress is purpose-built. Categories, tags, authors, comments, RSS, editorial workflow—all built-in. Durable can do blogs but it's not the primary focus.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Durable wins
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Generation speed</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          30 seconds. That's not marketing—that's what I measured. Enter your business info, Durable generates complete site with sections, images, AI copy, forms, CRM. 10Web takes 30-60 seconds just for initial generation.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">PageSpeed</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          My test sites: Durable scored 98/100 on PageSpeed. 10Web scored 78/100. WordPress overhead is real. Durable is optimized for speed out of the box—no caching plugins, no optimization work needed.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Built-in CRM</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Durable includes a CRM that automatically captures leads from forms. 10Web requires external CRM tools or plugins. For lead gen and simple business sites, Durable's all-in-one approach is convenient.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Simplicity</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Durable requires zero technical knowledge. Generate, review, publish. 10Web requires understanding WordPress concepts—themes, plugins, widgets, updates. Non-technical users find Durable much friendlier.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Real example: Local business site
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Built a local HVAC company site on both platforms:
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 space-y-4">
          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">10Web AI: 2 hours</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Generated in 45 seconds. Spent 90 minutes finding a theme that didn't look generic. 30 minutes configuring contact form plugin. Final site loaded in 2.1s. Functional but slow build process.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Durable AI: 10 minutes</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Generated in 30 seconds with HVAC-specific copy. Spent 5 minutes adjusting services section. 5 minutes adding phone number to header. Done. Loaded in 0.9s. Owner loved it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Real example: The WordPress exit that cost $4,000
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Three years ago, a client built their site on Durable. Simple service business, 5 pages. Last month they decided to scale—add blog, membership area, online courses. Needed WordPress features.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 space-y-4">
          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The problem</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Durable doesn't export. Zero code export. The entire site—copy, images, layout, CRM data—was locked in Durable's platform. To move to WordPress, they had to rebuild from scratch.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The rebuild</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Hired a developer. Copy-pasted all content manually. Recreated layouts in Elementor. Migrated CRM data to a new system. Total cost: $4,000 in development fees. 3 weeks of work. Lost revenue during migration.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="p-4 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300">
            <div class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">The alternative</div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              If they'd started with 10Web, migration would have been one-click export to standard WordPress. Any host, any developer, complete control. Cost would have been $0.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>The lesson:</strong> Durable is perfect if you know you'll never need WordPress features. But if there's ANY chance you'll need e-commerce, memberships, content-heavy features—start with 10Web. The rebuild cost is brutal.
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>Flip side:</strong> Another client built on 10Web three years ago. Still a simple service business. Never used the WordPress power. Paid 10Web hosting, dealt with plugin updates, managed backups. Could have saved $1,200+ with Durable's simpler approach.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A]">
          <p class="text-gray-900 font-medium">
            Choose Durable if you're 100% sure you'll never need WordPress.<br />
            Choose 10Web if there's ANY chance you'll scale beyond simple pages.<br /><br />
            Uncertainty costs $4,000 in rebuilds. Certainty saves money with the right tool.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>So which should you use?
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose 10Web if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You need real e-commerce (WooCommerce)</li>
          <li>You want plugin extensibility</li>
          <li>You care about code export/portability</li>
          <li>You're building a content-heavy site</li>
          <li>You have WordPress experience</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Durable if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You need a simple site fast</li>
          <li>PageSpeed matters more than features</li>
          <li>You're non-technical</li>
          <li>You want built-in CRM/lead capture</li>
          <li>You don't care about exporting</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Bottom line
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          10Web and Durable solve different problems. 10Web gives you WordPress power—extensible, portable, familiar, but complex and slower. Durable gives you speed—30-second generation, 95+ PageSpeed, zero technical knowledge required, but limited.<br /><br />
          For local businesses, simple portfolios, lead gen sites—Durable is perfect. For e-commerce, content sites, anything complex—10Web is the only viable choice.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
          <a href={comparisonData.tool1.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Read 10Web review
          </a>
          <a href={comparisonData.tool2.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Read Durable review
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

</Layout>
